f(x) = (x+1)^n-x^n-1
n \equiv 1 \mod 6
r
f(x)
f(x) = (x-r)^2q(x)
q(x)
f'(x) = 2(x-r)q(x) + (x-r)^2q(x).
f(r) = f'(r) = 0
r=e^{i\theta}
|r| = |r+1| = 1
r = -1/2 + i\sqrt3/2 = e^{i\pi/3}
r^{n-1}(r+1)-r^n=1 \implies r=\sqrt[n-1]1
(e^{i\pi/3})^{n-1} = 1
(n-1)\pi/3 = 2m\pi \implies n = 6m+1.
QED 
